  "texts": [
    "The advantage of R EXT Hα as a measure of Hα variability is that its definition does not depend on N obs, and hence the R EXT Hα results associated with different N obs values can be compared directly.",
    "From a statistical point of view, large sample size of stellar sources can compensate for small N obs, and this is the case in this study (see Figure 3).",
    "We evaluate the R EXT Hα values and their uncertainties (denoted by δR EXT Hα) based on Equation (5) for all the stellar sources in the MRS time-domain sample of solar-like stars employed in this work.",
    "The STD of R Hα fluctuation (denoted by R STD Hα) is also calculated for the sample, and the relationship between the values of R EXT Hα and R STD Hα will be discussed in Section 6.",
    "The data of the derived R EXT Hα and R STD Hα are available in the dataset of this work (see Appendix E)."
  ],
